scenario:
Design a prompt to generate JSON data for a social network, including users, friends, posts, and comments. The JSON output should have a structure as follows: 

```json
{
  "users": [
    {
      "id": "user1",
      "name": "John Doe",
      "friends": [
        "user2",
        "user3"
      ],
      "posts": [
        {
          "id": "post1",
          "content": "Hello, world!"
        },
        {
          "id": "post2",
          "content": "This is a sample post."
        }
      ],
      "comments": [
        {
          "id": "comment1",
          "postId": "post1",
          "content": "Nice post!"
        },
        {
          "id": "comment2",
          "postId": "post2",
          "content": "Great content!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "user2",
      "name": "Jane Doe",
      "friends": [
        "user1",
        "user3"
      ],
      "posts": [
        {
          "id": "post3",
          "content": "Hi, everyone!"
        }
      ],
      "comments": [
        {
          "id": "comment3",
          "postId": "post3",
          "content": "Hi, Jane!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "id": "user3",
      "name": "Bob Smith",
      "friends": [
        "user1",
        "user2"
      ],
      "posts": [
        {
          "id": "post4",
          "content": "Hello, world!"
        }
      ],
      "comments": [
        {
          "id": "comment4",
          "postId": "post4",
          "content": "Hi, Bob!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```
The target artifact type is JSON data. Constraints: The JSON output should be under 200 bytes, should include at least 3 users, and should not contain any duplicate IDs. The evaluation criteria are as follows:

* `adherence_to_constraints` (30 points): Does the generated JSON data adhere to the specified constraints?
* `json_syntax_validity` (25 points): Is the generated JSON data syntactically valid?
* `content_diversity` (45 points): Does the generated JSON data contain diverse content, including different user names, post contents, and comment contents?
